<tbody>

<!--  CONTENT -->

<tr>
<td colspan="3">
<div id="sectionDescription">The Screen Sharer is a simple tool for sharing any region on your computer screen with other users in a Wonderland world.</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-1.png" align="top">
Select "Share screen" from the Tools menu.
<div id="pix"><img src="ScreenShare/ToolsShareScreen.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
The Screen Sharer is also available from the "Insert Object" window. </div>
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-2.png" align="top">
A red border will appear in the upper left corner of your screen.
<div id="pix"><img src="ScreenShare/ShareBorder.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
You can move this border using the blue handle on the top of the border or you can resize the border using the blue resize corner.</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-3.png" align="top">
The area enclosed in the red border appears in the Screen Sharer application in world.
<div id="pix"><img src="ScreenShare/ShareScreen-inworld.png" width="200px">
</div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
This is a view-only application. Other users may not take control and interact with your screen. Note that the frame-rate is locked at 1 frame per second to avoid using excess bandwidth. </div>
</div>
</div>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-4.png" align="top">
Other users, however, may share their own screen. They do this by right-clicking on the Screen Sharer window and selecting "Start Sharing" from the context menu. <div id="pix"><img src="ScreenShare/ShareScreen-start.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
If someone else is already sharing, a confirmation dialog will appear confirming that you no longer wish to share the other person's screen.</div>
</div>
</td>

<td>
<div id="step">
<img src="BlueNumbers/Blue-5.png" align="top">
To stop sharing, either delete the Screen Sharer application or select "Stop Sharing" from the context menu.
<div id="pix"><img src="ScreenShare/ShareScreen-stop.png" width="200px"></div>
<div id="stepNoHang">
If you stop sharing, the window will turn gray and anyone else may select "Start Sharing" to show their screen.</div>
</div>
</div>
</td>


<!--       TIPS SECTION -->
<td>
<div id="sectionHead">Tips</div>

<div id="tipName">Screen Sharer Uses</div>
<div id="tip">Use the Screen Sharer to share presentations, spreadsheets, error logs, or other applications that do run natively in Wonderland. It is not, however, intended to share video or other real-time applications.</div>

<div id="tipName">Making Use of Two Monitors</div>
<div id="tip">If you have two monitors available, have your Wonderland window running on one and the area of the screen to share on the other.</div>

<div id="tipName">Pointer Stops Updating</div>
<div id="tip">If your pointer stops updating in the Screen Sharer window, click once on the Screen Sharer application in Wonderland and then resume working within the red border on your desktop.
</div>


</td>

</tr>
